{
  "stem": "25639.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I, I noticed that we were not as popular anymore as we used to be, and our-- eventually our closest non-Jewish friends had ignored us.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And this wasn't always the case, but it happened more and more frequently as time went by and anti-Semitism set in.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They started singing anti-Semitic songs, and these, these were usually words, anti-Semitic words, to existing melodious melodies.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So that, as children, we just wanted to sing the melody without paying too much attention to the harmful words to the song.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I remember one time, I came home and it could have been my sister, but I remember mother's reaction.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She said, what are you singing there?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So, I said, oh, the new song, and it made fun of the Jews.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You remember that?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[SINGING IN HUNGARIAN] Whoever has a Jewish girl for a girlfriend, [HUNGARIAN].",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That means that should tie a rope around his or her neck.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "These are-- but the-- you can hear the melody.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It's, it's very-- I started too low.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I'm a little bit hoarse right now.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But there were other songs, and my sister and I, when we get together, we, we remember these times.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "How was that affecting the children in your school, the other children toward you, non-Jewish children?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, naturally, we were not more popular, as you can well understand.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And soon, we were isolated.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We played dances.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We would-- we would stand in a large circle and somebody would pick up someone for a dance, and if you were Jewish, you weren't picked up.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You were not asked to be-- to dance.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And this may seem very unimportant and harmless, but as children, you feel hurt when you realize that you are no longer popular, and only because you are a Jew.",
      "word_count": 30
    }
  ],
